e by utilizing all elements of nursing process.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 3. Assess and evaluates patient's status by:      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. Assisting in feeding the patient as assigned.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. Regularly re-evaluating patient and family / caregiver needs      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C. Revising the plan of care as necessary      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 4. Initiates the plan of care and makes necessary revisions as patients status and needs change.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 5. Uses health assessment data to determine nursing diagnosis.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 6. Develops a care plan that establishes goals, based on nursing diagnosis and incorporates palliative nursing actions. Includes the patient and the family in the planning process.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 7. Initiates appropriate preventive and rehabilitative nursing procedures. Administers medications and Treatments as prescribed by the physician in the physician's plan of care.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 8. Counsels the patient and family in meeting nursing and related needs.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 9. Provides health care instructions to the patient as appropriate per assessment and plan.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 10. Assists the patient with the activities of daily living and facilitates the patient’s efforts toward self-sufficiency and optional comfort care.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark 11. Acts as Case Manager when assigned by Clinical Supervisor and assumes responsibility to coordinate patient care for assigned caseload.    br    br    .form-row.col-md-12      .form-group.col-md-6.text-center          .card              .card-body.bg-white                  div.flex.text-center                      div#sigbox(style="width:450px;")                          input#signature(name='pg5signature1' type='text' placeholder='Sign here' style="font-size:50px;")                  br                  h4.mt-0.header-title.text-center.text-dark SIGNATURE    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-12            h4.text-dark Communications        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 1. Completes, maintains and submits accurate and relevant clinical notes regarding patient’s condition and caregiven.Records pain / symptom management changes / outcomes as appropriate.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 2. Communicates with the physician regarding the patients needs and reports changes in the patients condition; obtains / receives physicians orders as required.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 3. Communicates with community health related persons to coordinate the care plan.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 4. Teaches The patient and family / caregiver self-care techniques as appropriate. Provides medication, diet and other instructions as ordered by the physician and recognizes and utilizes opportunities for health counseling with patients and families / caregivers.Works in concert with the other hospice interdisciplinary group members.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 5. Provides and maintains a safe environment for the patient.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 6. Assists the patient and family / caregiver and other team members in providing continuity of care        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 7. Works in cooperation with the family / caregiver and hospice interdisciplinary team members to meet the emotional needs of the patient nd family / caregiver.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 8. Attends interdisciplinary group meetings.    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-12          h4.text-dark Additional Duties        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 1. Participates in on-call duties as defined by the on-call policy.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 2. Ensures that arrangements for equipment and other necessary items and services are available.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 3. Supervises ancillary personnel and delegates responsibilities when required.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 4. Assumes responsibility for personal growth and development and maintains and upgrades professional knowledge and practice skills through attendance and participation in continuing education and inservice classes.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 5. Fullfills the obligation of requested and / or accepted case assignments        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark.text 6. Actively participates in quality management program.    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-group.col-md-6.text-center            .card                .card-body.bg-white                    div.flex.text-center                        div#sigbox(style="width:450px;")                            input#signature(name='pg5signature2' type='text' placeholder='Sign here' style="font-size:50px;")                    br                    h4.mt-0.header-title.text-center.text-dark SIGNATURE    br    br